gomodel:SYNGO_2735  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Wong et.al. use STED microscopy to demonstrate that Liprin a2 (gene product of PPFIA2) is localized in the presynaptic terminal. Diffuse signal was observed throughout the terminal.\n\nIn a separate experiment, knockout of the close homolog Liprin a3 led to a striking recruitment of Liprin a2 to the presynaptic active zone. This suggest that Liprin a2 may have a role at the active zone as well.\n\nSpecificity of the antibody for Liprin a2 was previously determined by Zurner et.al. 2011.. Experimental description: Primary mouse hippocampal cultures were generated from newborns as previously described (20), and all analyses were performed at DIV 14-17." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2735" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

